// Switchboard daemon <-> TUI client contract.
//
// Transport: gRPC over a single bidirectional connection.
//   - Local:  Unix domain socket  (switchboardd serve --socket <path>)
//   - Remote: `ssh <host> switchboardd dial-stdio` bridges stdio <-> the
//             remote daemon's Unix socket (the Docker-CLI dial-stdio pattern);
//             the client wraps that stdio as a net.Conn via grpc.WithContextDialer.
//
// One daemon instance serves exactly one host. The client connects to N daemons
// and is the source of truth for configs/groups/known-hosts (those are NOT in
// this contract — they live client-side). This contract covers what the daemon
// owns: sandbox lifecycle, the sbx option manifest, agent I/O, and the event stream.
